Step 6: Order Flow (Smart Routing)
User requests POST /orders { packageId: "esim_5GB_30D_EU_V3" } — no providerId:

OrdersService
  │
  ├── 1. Look up package in DB → get country, packageType, scopeType
  │
  ├── 2. ProviderRouterService.resolveOptimalProvider("FR", "DATA_WITH_ALL_UNLIMITED", "REGIONAL")
  │     ├── Filter healthy providers
  │     ├── Filter by supportedPackageTypes includes DATA_WITH_ALL_UNLIMITED
  │     ├── Filter by preferredRegions includes "EUROPE"
  │     ├── Sort by priority (lowest first)
  │     ├── Among equal priority, sort by cheapest wholesale price
  │     └── Return: "esim-go"
  │
  ├── 3. Dispatch to BullMQ with providerId = "esim-go"
  │
  └── 4. ActivationProcessor
        ├── Try esim-go (3 attempts)
        ├── If all fail → resolveOptimalProvider() excluding "esim-go"
        ├── Try fallback provider (2 attempts)
        └── If all fail → mark FAILED + webhook

