The key insight: providers don't know about your enums. The classification layer is entirely Atlantic's intelligence — it normalizes 6 different API shapes into one queryable model. The eSIM Go allowances array is the gold standard (explicit DATA/VOICE/SMS types). For providers that don't have that, you infer from whatever fields they expose.

